<p class="content-text">
In my humble opinion, I would say that this is one of the top pitching performances in all of
baseball. On June 23rd, 1971, Rick Wise pitched a no-hitter against the Reds at Riverfront Stadium,
only giving up a walk in the 6th inning. As you could have probably guessed by the 
title, Wise would end up hitting two home runs in that same game, being the only pitcher
to do so to this day. This video shows the final out of that game.
</p>

